definition: private/personal/interpersonal/sb with whom one has a close personal relationship/a member of one's clique

pinyin: xu1 ni3 si1 ren2 wang3 luo4

sentences.english: We need to unleash massive private investment in clean energy.
sentences.chinese: 我們必須在清潔能源方面發動大量的私人投資。

sentences.english: Into every life some rain must fall.
sentences.chinese: 每私人一生都得逢上陰雨。

sentences.english: Kerri: Yeah, he has a private pilot's license.
sentences.chinese: 會，他有私人飛行員執照。

sentences.english: I have no personal vendetta against Clarence Thomas.
sentences.chinese: 我沒有私人仇報克拉倫斯托馬斯。

sentences.english: It looks more a private club than a hotel lounge.
sentences.chinese: 那簡直就是一個高檔的私人商務會所。

sentences.english: But private investors may have been durably scared by the union's display of clout.
sentences.chinese: 但是私人投資者受到工會的這政治上的強烈恐嚇。

sentences.english: The gifts of charity meddled with a man's private affair.
sentences.chinese: 慈善團體的贈品受到了某人私人事務的干涉。

sentences.english: The Education Department said coaching was 'a private matter for parents'.
sentences.chinese: 州教育部說補習是家長們私人的事務。

sentences.english: They write of some very personal things.
sentences.chinese: 她們寫一些非常私人的東西。

sentences.english: Most gardens in Suzhou used to be private residences.
sentences.chinese: 蘇州的大多數園林過去是私人宅第。

sentences.english: The old servant led Mr Utterson through the laboratory and up some stairs to the doctor's private study above.
sentences.chinese: 老僕人帶他經過實驗室，上樓來到博士的私人書房。

sentences.english: I highly be pleottomd concerning the preceding manwis precious precise exercise.
sentences.chinese: 我高度賞玩後面那私人難得的切確演練。

sentences.english: Allow yourself time - everyday - for privacy, quiet, and introspection.
sentences.chinese: 每天自己一點私人時間安靜的反省。

sentences.english: Private Chinese donations have already raised more than $A520 million.
sentences.chinese: 中國的私人捐款已提出了多美元的a520萬美元。

sentences.english: Raia. He feels that the distribution system still gives preference to private institutions, he said.
sentences.chinese: 他說，他感覺分配系統仍然爲私人機構提供了優先權。

sentences.english: Oh, because the church is a private institution.
sentences.chinese: 因爲教堂是一個私人機構。

definition: to lease/to hire/to rent (sth from sb)
to keep hidden/to keep in one's private possession/secret store/stash
to borrow sth for another use/to borrow an idea for one's own use
